{
  "text": "however, there is no evidence for the formation of the 8 th generation. It seems to be that there is enough space for 256 phenylacetylenyl groups on the periphery of the 7 th generation, but not enough space for 512 phenylacetylenyl groups on the periphery of the 8 th generation [CITATION_1] . Since the 2-benzothiazolephenyloxy group is bulkier than a phenylethynyl group, only one chlorine atom of the terminal silyl group can be substituted by a 2-benzothiazoylphenyloxy group from the 1 st to 7 ",
